[{"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Oberfinanzdirektion K\u00f6ln S-2230 - 37 - St 111OFD Cologne S-2230 - 37 - St 111 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "23 2 1979EStG: 13EStG: 13aIncome tax assessment of farmers and foresters for the assessment period 1974 Accounting obligation1 Because of the limits at the beginning and end of the accounting obligation, see Section 127 (1) EStR 1975 For the determination of the amount of agricultural and (or) forestry assets, the new unit values \u200b\u200bare here according to the BewG 1965 plus the values \u200b\u200bfor leased areas"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "In the case of leased businesses, the total unit value (lessee and lessor share) is to be assumed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The part of this is attributable to the lessee that is attributable to the parts of the property used by him and contained in the unit value"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "In the case of the lessor, the leased assets are to be included if they represent business assets according to income tax principles"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Unit value Notifications about agricultural and forestry assets must always be evaluated promptly because of the possible effects on the accounting obligation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Increased deductions or special depreciations are to be considered when examining whether the provisions set out in Section 161 (1) no.1 lit."}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "e AO designated bookkeeping limit is exceeded, not to be considered (\u00a7 7a Abs 7 EStG 1975)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "This applies accordingly to the benefits in accordance with Sections 77 and 78 of the Income Tax Act (EStDV). Transfer of profits from agriculture and forestry according to average rates (Section 13a of the Income Tax Act). \u00a7 13a EStG entered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "According to Section 13a (1) of the Income Tax Act, taxpayers who are not obliged by law to keep books for an agricultural and forestry business and to regularly close accounts have a right to choose"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Upon request, you can determine your profit in accordance with Section 4 (1) EStG or 4 (3) EStG instead of determining your profits according to Section 13a Paragraphs 2 to 6 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Reference is made to Section 127 (3) EStR 1975"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "If such an application is not made, the profit must be determined in accordance with Section 13a Paragraphs 2 to 6 EStG if the basic amount (Section 13a Paragraph 3 EStG) is more than DM 0, see also Section 127 Paragraph 4 EStR 19753 Determination of the profit according to \u00a7 13a Abs 2 to 6 EStG The scheme for the determination of the profit according to \u00a7 13a Abs 2 to 6 EStG results from the form \"Annex ESt 2 L (74) - Determination of profits according to \u00a7 13a EStG\""}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "In detail, I would like to point out the following: 31 Basic amount The basic amount is to be determined in accordance with Section 13a (3) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Section 130a (3) EStR 1975 must be observed here"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The allocation of areas to the individual uses in the standard value method is also decisive when determining profit if the actual use at the beginning of the financial year deviates from this"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Such deviations can only be taken into account when the unit value is updated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "32 Value of the work performed With the basic amount according to \u00a7 13a Abs 3 EStG it is assumed that the business is managed exclusively with paid workers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The value of the work performed by the business owner and his relatives who are not employed in the business on the basis of an employment relationship, to be determined in accordance with Section 13a (4) of the Income Tax Act, must therefore be added to the basic amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Section 130 a Paragraph 4 to 6 EStR 1975 must be observed here"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "In Section 13a (4) No. 2 EStG, the term \"family members\" is the term \"relatives i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 10 StAnpG \"to be equated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "With the exception of minor work that is not carried out constantly, but only consists of doing something useful on the farm, the employees must work to an appropriate extent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The following must be observed in detail: 321 When determining the value of the work performance for the physical work of the owner and the relatives who are not employed, only the work performance is to be taken into account in the result that is based on the uses contained in the initial value according to Section 13a (3) EStG in individual cases not applicable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "322 If the initial value is a value share for special uses i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 13a Paragraph 3 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "1 c EStG, because the sum of the comparative or individual income values \u200b\u200battributable to these special uses does not exceed DM 4000 in total, no reduction by the percentage of full-time workers (VAK) attributable to special uses is required when determining the value of the work (see also footnote 4 on form \"Annex ESt 2 L (74)\")"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "In this case, when determining the maximum VAK to be applied according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Section 13 (4) no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "5 EStG to include the area of \u200b\u200bspecial uses in the relevant area of \u200b\u200bthe maximum permissible number of VAK"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "323 The value of the physical work performance of the business owner and his relatives employed in the business without an employment contract is, according to \u00a7 13a Para"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "5 EStG to be set at the most with the number of VAKs appropriate for the type and size of the establishment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "For areas of agricultural use, a maximum of 007 VAK per hectare are to be applied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "For the other values \u200b\u200bshown in the relevant unit value of the agricultural and forestry business (Section 13a Paragraph 3 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "1 letters b and c EStG), the appropriate number of VAKs must be determined in each individual case in accordance with Section 130 a para. 5 EStR 1975"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "This special determination is practically only necessary if hectare values \u200b\u200bof the lowest land or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Comparative values \u200b\u200b/ individual yield values \u200b\u200bfor special uses are included in the initial value (Section 13a (3) EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "However, this special determination of VAK can generally be dispensed with for the sake of simplification - unless the Stpfl requests otherwise"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Proceed according to line 24 and footnote 6 in the \"Annex ESt 2 L (74)\" form"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "324 For the appropriate number of VAK for the business owner and the relatives employed without an employment contract, paid full-time workers are to be taken into account according to the duration of their employment (\u00a7 13a para. 4 no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "5 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "This applies not only to permanently employed workers, but also to temporary workers employed on a short-term basis as well as to workers who are called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Contractors have been made available for certain ordering, maintenance or harvesting work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "For the crediting of the paid VAK, if necessary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "a breakdown of the wages, insofar as what) is applicable to the uses contained in the initial value (Section 13a (3) EStG) and b) to the uses not contained therein, is required"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The partial amount a) is to be taken into account when calculating the maximum amount of the value of the work performed by the business owner and relatives who are not employed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The partial amount b) is to be deducted as operating expenses when calculating the profit for the uses to which it is attributable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "325 If Stpfl does not provide any or obviously incorrect information on the scope of employment in the income tax declaration (form \"Annex L\"), the (physical) work performance of the business owner, the relatives employed in the business and (or) the paid workers are in proportion of (possibly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "to be estimated) different labor requirements for the individual parts of the company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The table in the Felsmann commentary, section C 27 (p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "523), serve as a guide for the average labor requirement in special branches of business"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "326 Example for calculating the value of work performance (Section 13a (4) EStG) - s"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Annex -33 Lease interest received Reference is made to Section 13a (5) sentence 3 EStG and Section 130a (7) EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "34 Surcharges according to Section 13a (6) EStG Reference is made to Section 13a (6) EStG and Section 130a (8) EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "In addition, please note: Surcharges are possible for a) special uses i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 13a Paragraph 6 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "1 EStG (to be entered in line 32 of the form \"Annex ESt 2 L (74)\", b) forestry use (to be entered in line 33 of the above"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Form), c) other operational processes that were not taken into account when determining the initial value, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Additional profits from the sale of breeding cattle and other particularly valuable animals, profits from transport services, profits from renting rooms to holiday guests and camping sites (ESt-Kartei NW, \u00a7 13 EStG, A Nr 82) and profits from the sale or removal of land (to be entered in line 34 of the above"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Form)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The surcharges are generally to be determined by comparing the operating income and operating expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "If no records are available, the profits (additional profits) are to be estimated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "When estimating the profits (additional profits) from sales of breeding cattle and other particularly valuable animals as well as from vegetable growing and intensive fruit growing in the context of horticultural use, the following guidelines can serve as a guide; their application must not lead to an obviously incorrect taxation (see BFH judgment of December 16, 1965 BStBl 1966 III p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "193)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "341 Sales of breeding animals and other particularly valuable animals As additional profits from the sale of breeding animals and other especially valuable animals"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "the amount by which the sales proceeds exceed the following starting values: Breeding bulls --------------------------- 1800 DM breeding cows ------- ---------------------- 1600 DM breeding cattle ------------------------- - 1400 DM breeding boars and sows ------------------ 600 DM breeding and riding horses ----------------- 3,000 DM wages for paid workers are taken into account here, so they cannot be deducted separately"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The same procedure is then to be followed if above-average prices are obtained for breeding animals other than those specified or for other valuable animals"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The initial value to be used in these cases results from the tax production costs of the animal species in question plus an assumed profit surcharge of 20% included in the initial value for the area under normal animal husbandry"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "342 Vegetable growing (horticultural use) For the delimitation of vegetable growing (horticultural use) from vegetable growing within the framework of agricultural use, see Section 607, Paragraph 1, No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "1 BewRL 1964 If vegetable growing is included in agricultural use, a surcharge in accordance with Section 13a (6) EStG cannot be considered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "In the case of vegetable growing (horticultural use), the net profit can be 40 to 65 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "of sales can be estimated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The profit is influenced by the type of marketing (auction in the wholesale market, sale on the farm, sale on the weekly market) and the wage expenditure"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The turnover fluctuates between 10,000 and 50,000 DM per hectare"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "You are dependent on z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "of soil quality, calculation options, under glass areas, number of harvests"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "343 Fruit growing (horticultural use) In the case of fruit growing (horticultural use), the net profit can be reduced to 30 to 50 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "of sales can be estimated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The profit is influenced by the type of marketing (auction in the wholesale market, sale on the farm, sale on the weekly market) and the wage expenditure"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The turnover fluctuates between 15,000 and 35,000 DM per hectare"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "They depend on the quality of the soil, climate and the age structure of the orchard"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "35 Value in use of the business owner's apartment When determining the profit, the value in use of the business owner's apartment in accordance with Section 13a (5) no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "5 EStG with one eighteenth of the flat value specifically shown in the unit value"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The residential part includes the buildings and parts of the building insofar as they are used by the owner of the business, the family members belonging to his household and the senior citizens for residential purposes (Section 34 (3) BewG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "If the right of residence of the retirees is secured in rem, the value of the apartment must be reduced proportionally - according to the ratio of the living space provided to the total area"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "In this case, a deduction of the value of the rented apartment as special expenses (permanent burden) is not possible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "36 Lease interest paid, interest owed, ongoing charges Reference is made to Section 13a (2) sentence 2 EStG and Section 130a (9) EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "37 Other additions and reductions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The following can be considered: additions and deductions according to \u00a7 6c EStG, expenses for the construction of farm workers' apartments, tax breaks according to \u00a7 78 EStDV, increased deductions for residential buildings according to \u00a7\u00a7 7b, 54 EStG i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "V with \u00a7 52 EStDV In the case of increased deductions and special depreciation, \u00a7 7a Paragraph 6 in conjunction with"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "V with \u00a7 52 Abs 10 EStG 1975 to be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Estimation of the profit of farmers who are obliged to keep accounts but do not keep proper books4 According to Section 127 (2) EStR, the profit of farmers and foresters who are obliged to keep accounts but do not keep proper books must be estimated on a case-by-case basis"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "With this estimate according to \u00a7 217 AO the actual profit of the business year should be recorded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "All circumstances of the individual case must be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Which estimation method is to be used in each individual case is left to the discretion of the tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "5 If, in individual cases, an estimation method tailored to the particular operational conditions is not to be preferred, or if the accounting results of comparable businesses or empirical records are not available, the profit is to be determined as follows: Starting amount (No. 62) Rent received (No. 63) Surcharges for not with the Starting amount, paid winnings or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Additional profits (No. 64) Value in use of the apartment (No. 65)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Wage expenses (No. 66)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Lease interest paid, interest on debt, permanent burdens (No. 67)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Other reductions (No. 68) = profit for the financial year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "For this purpose, the following is determined in detail: 61 General The following guidelines are only intended to serve as a guide for an accurate estimate of the profit (Section 127 (2) sentence 2 EStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "They must not lead to an obviously incorrect taxation (see BFH judgment of 16 December 1965 BStBl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "1966 III p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "193)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "62 Starting amount The starting amount per hectare of LN for the 1974/75 marketing year is: 621 for arable farms (grassland share up to 30 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "der LN) with a root crop portion of a) 15%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "and more of the LN --------------- 1400 DMb) less than 15 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "the LN ------------ 1200 DM 622 for mixed farms (grassland share 31 to 70%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "derLN) with a root crop portion of a) 15%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "and more of the LN --------------- 1100 DMb) less than 15 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "the LN ------------ 1000 DM 623 in pasture farming (grassland share 71%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "and more derLN) --------------------------------------- 1000 DM624 for sugar beet farms (more root crops than 25 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "the LN, sugar beet content more than 20%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "the LN) ------------------------------------------- 1800 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The agricultural area (LN) only includes the pure agricultural production areas, areas for buildings, courtyards, paths, ditches, field borders, water, land, quarries, sand pits and the like"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Areas are therefore not considered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Areas for house gardens are also not included"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Otherwise, Section 124 a Paragraph 3 EStR applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "For the calculation of the relevant root crop or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The proportion of grassland depends on the extent of this proportion in the respective marketing year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The areas under cultivation of root crops do not include those areas on which root crops are only grown as catch crops or as catch crops"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "63 Lease interest received Lease interest received, reduced by proportionate operating expenses, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Property tax paid must be added to the starting amount if it is included in income from agriculture and forestry"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "This is the case if the leased assets are part of the lessor's agricultural and forestry business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "64 surcharges for winnings or winnings not settled with the starting amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "All profits from sustainable or one-off operating income that are not included in the starting amount are to be added to the starting amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Such surcharges come z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Consideration for additional profits from sales of breeding cattle and other particularly valuable animals, profits from above normal cattle husbandry, additional profits from special crops, profits from other special branches of business, profits from the sale of land (see also Section VI - Special operating income - in the \"Appendix L\" form)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The surcharges are generally to be determined by comparing the operating income and operating expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "If no records are available, the profits (additional profits) are to be estimated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The following guidelines can serve as a guide: 641 Sales of breeding cattle and other particularly valuable animalsNo 341 applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "642 Abnormal animal husbandry Profits from animal breeding and husbandry are compensated with the initial value for the area, provided that the average \"customary\" animal population is not exceeded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Normal animal husbandry is to be used for ---------- fodder farms and other farms with a farm size of up to 20 ha LN ------------ 16 HA ----- --- 14 HA over 20 to 30 ha LN --- 14 HA -------- 12 HA over 30 to 50 ha LN ---- 12 HA -------- 10 HA over 50 ha LN ----------- 10 HA -------- 08 HAF forage farms are holdings where the forage area is 60 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "and more of the usable agricultural area (LN) without courtyard and building area, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "matters"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "In this context, the forage area includes: meadows (incl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Tree meadows, litter meadows), cattle pastures and arable meadows, as well as the cultivation areas for clover in pure seed and mixed cultivation, clover grass, alfalfa, seradella, Esparsette, green corn, vetches, sweet lupins and all other forage plants"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "When calculating the number of animals and converting them into livestock units (VE), section 124 a (2) EStR 1975 must be used"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "No animals may be recorded twice"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "When determining the number of VE for fattening animals - with the exception of beef cattle - regular and sustainable production in the marketing year is to be assumed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "I have no concerns if, as a rule, the total number of animals produced (sold or consumed) in the marketing year is determined and this number is multiplied by the relevant conversion key"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "When determining the number of VE, it is assumed that the other animals are kept regularly and sustainably during the marketing year and that the annual average population is assumed for beef cattle"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "In general, it is sufficient if half the total of the respective opening and closing balance is determined and multiplied by the relevant conversion key"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "For the excess inventory remaining after the normal inventory has been taken into account, the following is to be set as profit for the 1974/75 financial year: As a rule ---------------------------- 400 DM per unit - with exclusive rearing and keeping of fattening poultry, depending on marketing, 100 to 200 DM per unit, laying hens depending on marketing 200 to 300 DM per unit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The amounts deviating from the standard rate can also be used as a guide if the animals are kept predominantly by the aforementioned animals"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Wages for paid workers are taken into account here, so they cannot be deducted separately"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "643 Field vegetable cultivation Field vegetable cultivation means the cultivation of vegetables according to the agricultural cultivation method within the framework of the agricultural crop rotation in annual cultivation and as a reproduction after previous other agricultural use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "According to my findings, a profit of DM 3,600 per hectare was generally achieved in the 1974/75 marketing year from the cultivation of vegetables in the fields"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "To determine the additional profit to be added, this amount is to be reduced by the starting amount per hectare of LN (see No. 62)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Wages for paid workers are taken into account here, so they cannot be deducted separately"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "If lower revenues have been achieved, the taxpayer is free to provide evidence of the actual revenues"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "In these cases, a deduction of 30% can be made without special proof of business expenses (excluding external wages)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "be acknowledged"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The remaining amount is to be reduced accordingly by the starting amount for the field vegetable cultivation area (as above)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "644 Vegetable growing (horticultural use) No. 342 applies accordingly to the determination of profit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "As a surcharge on the starting amount, however, only the additional profit, i.e."}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "the profit reduced by the pro-rata starting amount applied in the individual case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "645 Fruit growing (horticultural use) No. 343 applies accordingly to the determination of profit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "As a surcharge on the starting amount, however, only the additional profit, i.e."}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "the profit reduced by the pro-rata starting amount applied in the individual case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "65 Value in use of the apartment In accordance with Section 13 Paragraph 2 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "2 EStG also the value in use of the taxpayer's apartment if the apartment does not exceed the size customary for businesses of the same type"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "651 The BFH has repeatedly (judgments of 30 Jan"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "1974 - BStBl 1974 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "608 from Jan 31"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "1974 - BStBl 1975 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "3 and from March 28, 1974 - BStBl 1975 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "9) commented on how the value in use of the apartment i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 13 Paragraph 2 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "2 EStG is to be determined"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Thereafter, the basis for estimating the gross rental value - such as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "also when applying the value in use of the apartment in the context of determining income from commercial operations or renting and leasing - the usual local average rent for apartments of a comparable type, location and equipment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "If a comparative rent cannot be determined, the value in use of the apartment must be estimated based on the cost rent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "A discount of 20 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "for the general restriction of the usability of an apartment on the farm and an additional discount of up to 30%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "due to individual impairment of the value in use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "652 To simplify matters, individual determinations can be dispensed with for financial years ending after December 31, 1974 in the following cases: a) Value in use of the apartment in before January 1"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Buildings erected in 1964 There are no concerns if the value in use according to the unit valuation according to the value ratios on 1 Jan"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Determinations made in 1964 are measured"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The assumed annual rent is to be assumed, reduced by the discounts taken into account in the unit valuation according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Section 47 sentences 2 and 3 BewG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The resulting amount is 40 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "to be increased and recognized as value in use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Are on buildings built before Jan 1"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "1964, after Dec."}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "In 1963, considerable modernizations were carried out, which, according to the rent index of the valuation offices, led to a higher rental price for the square meter of living space according to the value ratios on 1 Jan"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "1964, the applicable annual rent is to be applied, taking into account the higher rent according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "To recalculate rent index"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "b) Value in use of the apartment after 31 Dec."}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Buildings manufactured in 1963 There are no concerns about reducing the usage value to 5%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "to estimate the acquisition or production costs attributable to the apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "However, the value in use according to a) must not be undercut"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "If the determination of the value in use of the apartment in accordance with the above regulation leads to incorrect taxation in the long term, the value in use must be determined in accordance with the principles set out in No. 651"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Inappropriate taxation is to be assumed as a rule if high expenses (especially high debt interest) would result in a loss as the value in use of the apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "When applying these simplification rules, all expenses related to the apartment - including the costs for cosmetic repairs - are to be deducted as operating expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "66 Wage expenses The starting amount (No. 62) is based on the assumption that the business is managed exclusively with unpaid workers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Wage expenses are therefore to be deducted from the starting amount, insofar as they are attributable to the profit settled with the starting amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Wage expenses incurred with profits or wages not paid for in the starting amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Additional profits (see No. 64) are to be taken into account when calculating the surcharges required for this"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "when estimating these surcharges"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "compensated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "For the individual cases"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "required allocation of wage expenses is to apply No. 324 and No. 325 accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The wage expenses to be deducted include not only the expenses of the permanently employed workers, but also the expenses for short-term temporary workers and for the workers who are"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Contractors have been made available for certain ordering, maintenance or harvesting work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "If wage expenses cannot be proven, an estimate e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "possible according to documents from comparable companies"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "67 Lease interest paid, interest on debts, permanent charges can be deducted if they are operating expenses and have not already been taken into account when determining the surcharges according to No. 64"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "68 Other reductions As such,"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Expenses for the construction of farm workers' apartments and increased deductions for residential buildings according to \u00a7\u00a7 7b, 54 EStG come into consideration"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "In the case of increased deductions and special depreciation, \u00a7 7a Paragraph 6 i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "V with \u00a7 52 Abs 10 EStG 1975 to be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Book-keeping farmers and foresters 71 Average livestock values \u200b\u200bThe current average livestock values \u200b\u200bremain unchanged"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The established cattle average values \u200b\u200bfor horses only apply to work horses, the values \u200b\u200bfor other horses (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Breeding or riding horses) are to be determined separately"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "72 Value in use of apartment No. 65 applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Other 81 Control notifications Except in the usual cases (control notifications for the purposes of the Bp, the recording of taxable transactions with other taxpayers, inheritance tax), I ask you to prepare control notifications in the following cases: or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "to disclose circumstances arising from the files that may affect the level of the fixed unit values \u200b\u200b(e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Change in areas for special use, changes in animal populations)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "b) In particular, cases without signal \"A\", in which wage expenses are asserted, and cases with considerable wage expenses are to be reported to the responsible income tax office for examination by the income tax field audit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "This also applies if wage expenses are estimated at the profit determination"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "82 Consultation of the valuation files when carrying out the assessment In particular when determining profits in accordance with Section 13a of the Income Tax Act and in valuation cases, I ask that you refer to the assessment files for the assessment and review of the values \u200b\u200bto be applied in the individual case when calculating profits"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "The system was not included"}, {"meta": {"name": "0025187.xml"}, "text": "Income tax / wage tax / church tax North Rhine-Westphalia agriculture"}]